Ithaca, N.Y.

October 15, 1954

Dear Laughlin,

Thanks for your letter. I understand your point and shall in all probability take your advice regarding publication abroad.1 Any concrete suggestions you would care to make regarding such publication would be appreciated.

Before I ship her to France, I would like to show L. to Farrar, Straus & Young, 101 Fifth Avenue. A short while ago Mr. Straus wrote me and asked to read my latest. Would you please do me the favor of forwarding the MS to